<!-- +++++++++++ Physical_unit_interconnect_definition +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Physical_unit_interconnect_definition_arm.Physical_unit_interconnect_definition">
	A <b>Physical_unit_interconnect_definition</b> is a type of 
	<express_ref linkend="Part_view_definition:arm:Part_view_definition_arm.Part_view_definition"/> 
	A <b>Physical_unit_interconnect_definition</b> is referenced by members of 
	<express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_interconnect_definition:arm:Physical_unit_interconnect_definition_arm.Connector_based_interconnect_definition"/>  
	that correspond to the mated connectors for the sub assemblies included in the design.  
	A <b>Physical_unit_interconnect_definition</b> does not include the detailed wiring definition of the cables and assemblies included.  
	A <b>Physical_unit_interconnect_definition</b> does not include the mating conditions or geometric information needed to describe the position 
	and orientation of the items in the <b>Physical_unit_interconnect_definition</b>.
</ext_description>

<!-- WR1 -->
<ext_description linkend="Physical_unit_interconnect_definition_arm.Physical_unit_interconnect_definition.wr:WR1">
	Each 
	<express_ref linkend="Assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Product_occurrence_definition_relationship"/> 
	that references the <b>Physical_unit_interconnect_definition</b> as a 
	<express_ref linkend="Assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Product_occurrence_definition_relationship.relating_view"/> 
	shall be a complex of both a 
	<express_ref linkend="Assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage"/> 
	and a 
	<express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Next_assembly_usage_occurrence_relationship"/> 
	or the
	<express_ref linkend="Assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Product_occurrence_definition_relationship"/> 
	shall not be either a 
	<express_ref linkend="Assembly_structure:arm:Assembly_structure_arm.Next_assembly_usage"/> 
	or a 
	<express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_design_view:arm:Physical_unit_design_view_arm.Next_assembly_usage_occurrence_relationship"/>.
</ext_description>


<!-- +++++++++++ Connector_based_interconnect_definition +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Physical_unit_interconnect_definition_arm.Connector_based_interconnect_definition"><p>
A <b>Connector_based_interconnect_definition</b> is the linkage between two physical connectors 
that specifies the existence of a mated state of that pair of connectors in the context
of an assembly that includes the components related to the connectors.  
The connectors each are part of an item in the product for which the <express_ref linkend="Physical_unit_interconnect_definition:arm:Physical_unit_interconnect_definition_arm.Physical_unit_interconnect_definition"/> 
referenced by <b>associated_definition</b> is a definition.
</p><note>
A <b>Connector_based_interconnect_definition</b> can be considered to be a minimal or high-level depiction of the linkage between the items included in the product.
</note> 
<example>
Consider a case where a computer supplier provides a detached cable between a monitor and a computer as part of a kit.
The kit includes at least the following three items: a cable, a monitor and a computer.
A <b>Connector_based_interconnect_definition</b> for connecting the computer to the monitor 
cable would indicate a linkage between the 'video out' connector on the computer and the 'computer' connector on the monitor cable.
</example>
</ext_description>
